revision.text: Possibly: Entick's New Latin-English Dictionary, designed for the use of Grammar Schools, and Private Education: containing All the Words and Phrases proper for Reading the Classic Authors in Both Languages. Accurately collected from the most approved Latin Authors. Accompanied with every Improvement to supply the Deficiencies of other Dictionaries, and to enable the Scholar to parse and construe each Word according to its various interpretations by the best Authors in the English tongue. By William Crakelt, M. A. Rector of Nursted and Ifield in Kent. (John Entick). (London : Printed for Charles Dilly, M DCC LXXXVI. [1786]). http://library.st-andrews.ac.uk/record=b2452726~S1
